description:
&lt;p&gt;The Margaret Centre is pleased to announce a full time 5 position to join our team. We are looking for an enthusiastic and experience nurse to join our GOLD Standard framework Unit. The Margaret Centre has 11 beds where we deliver holistic care of patients with advanced progressive illness. The management of pain and other symptoms and provision of psychological, social and spiritual support is paramount. The goal of the unit is achieve of the best quality of end of life care for patients and those important to them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe and compassionate care at the end of life by identifying patients in the last year, months and weeks of life. For every patient under our care we will always put the needs and wishes of the patient and his/her loved ones first.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve our vision we have 6 ambitions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Each person is cared for as an individual.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Each person gets fair access to care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maximising comfort and well-being.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care is co-ordinated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All staff are prepared to care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Each community is prepared to help.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For futher details/informal visit please contact: Fiona McLoughlin (SSR) on 02085356604 or email fiona.mcloughlin2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
